entries.description: Contract used to update the verifier and keep track of current and old versions.

entries.name: L1MessageQueueV2
entries.description: Contains the array of queued L1 -> L2 messages, either appended using the L1ScrollMessenger or the EnforcedTxGateway.

entries.name: L1ERC721Gateway
entries.description: Contract used to bridge ERC721 tokens from L1 to L2.

entries.name: L1ScrollMessenger
entries.description: Contract used to send L1 -> L2 and relay messages from L2. It allows to replay failed messages and to drop skipped messages. L1 -> L2 messages sent using this contract pay for L2 gas on L1 and will have the aliased address of this contract as the sender.

entries.name: EnforcedTxGateway
entries.description: Contracts to force L1 -> L2 messages with the proper sender.

paused.description: Whether the sendTransaction function is paused or not. Affects the sequencer failure risk.

entries.name: ScrollOwner
entries.description: Owner of all contracts in the system. It implements an extension of AccessControl that manages roles and functions allowed to be called by each role.
